modules.description: The interpreter evaluates expressions and executes control flow constructs like loops and conditionals in templates, leveraging abstract syntax trees, variable-context mappings, and mutable interpreter state to manage dynamic data and scoped variables. It supports stateful transformations through context saving, rewinding, and scoped assignments, alongside template-specific operations such as include handling, cycle iteration, and incremental value updates. This facilitates rendering data-driven content with nested logic, modular file inclusion, and isolated variable scopes for templating workflows.

This module provides functions to create a loop context for iterating over sequences and to generate a request value for handling HTTP-like inputs. It operates on Liquid syntax values and contexts, enabling dynamic variable binding during template execution. Concrete use cases include processing loop iterations in templates and injecting request-specific data into the evaluation context.

The interpreter evaluates Liquid templates by processing expressions, control flow, and scoped variables using abstract syntax trees and mutable state. It supports operations like template inclusion, loop iteration, and context management for dynamic content rendering. Interpreter_objects provides utilities to create loop contexts and handle HTTP-like request data, enabling dynamic variable binding during template execution.
